      <h2>Memory moves <em>with the herd.</em></h2>
      <div class="hero-poem">
        <p>Before the road was a road, it was a route &mdash; walked by hooves and feet, marked by wells and the memory of where the rain fell last. Every season folded into the next, carried in songs, in saddle-bags, in the names given to a hundred different grasses.</p>
        <p>This archive is a resting place for that knowledge: gathered, not owned. We hold it here so the walking is not forgotten.</p>
