            <img src="images/Rabari/culture/embodiery-of-kutch.png" alt="Kutch embroidery">
          </div>
          <span class="media-tag">Gujarat & Rajasthan, India</span>
        </div>
        <div class="community-text">
          <div class="eyebrow">Community Profile</div>
          <h4>The Rabari</h4>
          <span class="region">Western India &middot; Camel &amp; Sheep Pastoralists</span>
          <p>The Rabari are a pastoral community of Gujarat and Rajasthan, long associated with the breeding of camels, sheep, and goats across the arid tracts of Kachchh and the Thar's eastern edge. Oral tradition traces their migration into the region over several centuries.</p>
          <p>Rabari migratory cycles, locally remembered through named halting grounds and well sites, have historically followed the retreat and return of monsoon grasses. Recent decades have seen these cycles disrupted by the shrinking of common grazing land.</p>
          <div class="tag-row">
            <span>Camel Pastoralism</span>
            <span>Kachchh</span>
            <span>Grazing Commons</span>
          </div>
          <a href="#gallery" class="read-link">View Rabari Images &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>

