          </div>
          <span class="media-tag">Afghanistan Highlands</span>
        </div>
        <div class="community-text">
          <div class="eyebrow">Community Profile</div>
          <h4>The Kuchi</h4>
          <span class="region">Afghanistan &middot; Goat &amp; Sheep Pastoralists</span>
          <p>The Kuchi are Afghanistan's largest pastoral nomadic population, historically moving between summer highland pastures and lower winter grazing grounds across a route system that predates the country's modern borders.</p>
          <p>Decades of conflict, drought, and shifting land tenure have reshaped Kuchi migration substantially, pushing many families toward partial or full settlement near urban peripheries.</p>
          <div class="tag-row">
            <span>Highland Migration</span>
            <span>Kin-Based Herding</span>
            <span>Displacement</span>
          </div>
